modules.description: This module supports constructing and transforming structured representations of OCaml values with explicit handling of shared references and lazy evaluation, enabling precise syntax-directed pretty-printing. It operates on a structured type that models primitives, containers, tuples, records, and algebraic data types, while providing combinators to map over collections and control sharing behavior. Typical applications include debugging complex data structures with preserved sharing semantics or generating human-readable OCaml syntax from in-memory values for tooling purposes.
